# Mongoose Model Conventions

## Schema Definition

- Define the TypeScript interface first, then the Mongoose schema
- Use `mongoose.models.ModelName || mongoose.model()` pattern to avoid recompilation in dev
- Add indexes via separate `.index()` calls on the schema
- Use `timestamps: true` for automatic `createdAt`/`updatedAt`

## Pattern

```typescript
import mongoose, { Schema, Document } from "mongoose";

export interface IModelName extends Document {
  field: string;
  // ...
}

const modelNameSchema = new Schema<IModelName>(
  {
    field: { type: String, required: true },
  },
  { timestamps: true }
);

modelNameSchema.index({ field: 1 });

export const ModelName =
  mongoose.models.ModelName ||
  mongoose.model<IModelName>("ModelName", modelNameSchema);
```

